---
import Chapter from '../layouts/Chapter.astro';
const lds = [{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Buying", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/buying"}]}];
---
<Chapter
  title="Buying — Patrick Milhaupt · North Shore"
  description="A buyer-side practice built on the pre-MLS pipeline, institutional comp analysis, and negotiation discipline drawn from a deep DOM library across the North Shore corridor."
  path="/buying" current="/buying" palette="0.35"
  jsonLd={lds.length>=1 ? lds[0] : null}
  rail={[{"id": "ch-00", "num": "00", "label": "Opening"}, {"id": "ch-01", "num": "01", "label": "Discovery"}, {"id": "ch-02", "num": "02", "label": "Off-Market"}, {"id": "ch-03", "num": "03", "label": "Negotiation"}, {"id": "ch-04", "num": "04", "label": "Begin"}]}
>


  <section class="chapter" id="ch-00" data-chapter="0" data-palette="0.10">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="hashmark"><i></i></span>
        <div class="meta" style="border:0; padding:0;">
          <span class="eyebrow">Buying &middot; North Shore</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h1 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Buyer-side <em>representation</em>.
      </h1>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        A buyer-side practice built on the Sotheby's pre-MLS network, institutional comp analysis, and the conviction that the right home never looks like a deal at the table &mdash; it looks <em>extraordinary</em> in retrospect. <strong>The math has to come first.</strong>
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <a class="btn" href="#ch-01">Walk through the process &darr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-01" data-chapter="1" data-palette="0.30">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">01</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter One</span>
          <span class="sub">Discovery</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Brief, then <em>baseline</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        We open with a long-form discovery brief &mdash; village preferences, school constraints, architectural taste, price band, and the deal-breakers nobody writes down. Then a baseline against the live market with the same dashboard I read every morning. By the end of the first conversation you'll have a target-price range that holds up against a five-year baseline &mdash; not a Zillow estimate.
      </p>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step"><span class="n">STEP &middot; 01</span><div><div class="t">Discovery Brief</div><div class="d">A long-form conversation about what you actually want vs. what the spec sheet says you want. Architectural taste, school constraint, lakefront vs. ravine vs. east-of-Sheridan, the price beyond which you don't care.</div></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="n">STEP &middot; 02</span><div><div class="t">Live Market Baseline</div><div class="d">The same dashboard I read every morning &mdash; median, DOM, SP/OLP, absorption &mdash; filtered to your village + price band. You'll see exactly where the market is before you fall in love with anything.</div></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="n">STEP &middot; 03</span><div><div class="t">ZenList Activation</div><div class="d">Complimentary Sotheby's pre-MLS access activated for your search. Curated listings arrive in your inbox before they reach public portals &mdash; sometimes by 48 hours.</div></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-02" data-chapter="2" data-palette="0.55">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">02</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter Two</span>
          <span class="sub">Off-Market</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        The market <em>before</em> the market.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        The Sotheby's pre-MLS network and an internal pipeline of "owners considering" surface a meaningful number of homes each year before they reach the public market. For buyers with a clear brief, this is often where the match happens &mdash; quietly, before competition sets the terms.
      </p>
      <div class="lock-card fade-up">
        <div class="lock-row">
          <span class="pad" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
              <rect x="4" y="11" width="16" height="10" rx="2"></rect>
              <path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0110 0v4"></path>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <h3>Access by introduction</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="l">
          Sotheby's Pre-MLS Network &middot; <span>free for active buy-side clients</span><br>
          Activate at <a href="https://zenlist.realestate" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--gold-lit,#E0BC7E)">zenlist.realestate</a> &middot; updated every two minutes from the live MLS feed.
        </div>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/contact">Request activation</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-03" data-chapter="3" data-palette="0.75">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">03</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter Three</span>
          <span class="sub">Negotiation</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        The <em>number</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        Every offer goes out backed by three independent valuation methods &mdash; sales comparison, replacement cost, and income-equivalent &mdash; that have to converge before I'll endorse the number. From there it's days-on-market analysis on the comparable set, list-to-original-list ratio analysis, and a tailored negotiation built around the specific motivations of the listing side, not the market average. Institutional discipline applied at the table on your behalf.
      </p>
      <div class="kpi-grid">
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">National Standing</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">Top 2%</span><span class="d up">RealTrends Verified Top Agent &middot; 2024</span></div>
        <div class="kpi pop"><span class="l">Valuation methods</span><span class="v">3</span><span class="d up">Sales comp &middot; Replacement cost &middot; Income-equivalent</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Inspection negotiation</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">Line-item</span><span class="d">49 closing-checklist items</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Appraisal defense</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">Built in</span><span class="d up">Pre-emptive evidence package</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-04" data-chapter="4" data-palette="1.00">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="num">04</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Begin</span>
          <span class="sub">A 30-minute call</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Begin a <em>brief</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        Thirty minutes. We'll walk through your brief, baseline you against the live market, and decide together whether a representation conversation makes sense for your search.
      </p>
      <div class="begin-block fade-up">
        <div class="col"><div class="l">Direct</div><div class="v"><a href="tel:+18478499828" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;">(847) 849-9828</a></div></div>
        <div class="col"><div class="l">Email</div><div class="v"><a href="mailto:pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com">pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com</a></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center; margin-top: 32px;">
        <a class="btn" href="mailto:pmilhaupt@jamesonsir.com">Schedule the Call &rarr;</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/">Back to the story</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


</Chapter>
